PN,31801
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1781823786
OL,3,CHot with humid air: Temperatures set
OL,4,Cto reach close to 30-32C
OL,6,FTemperatures in parts of the UK are
OL,7,Fgoing up over the next few days,
OL,8,Fcreating heatwave conditions for some
OL,9,Fof us.
OL,11,FIt means summer is set to return just
OL,12,Fin time for the Summer Solstice this
OL,13,Fweekend, where the days are at their
OL,14,Flongest, allowing maximum daytime
OL,15,Fheating in a string of mid-June
OL,16,Fsunshine.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1781823786
OL,3,CHot with humid air: Temperatures set
OL,4,Cto reach close to 30-32C
OL,6,FSearing heat from Europe will seep
OL,7,Finto parts of the UK in the coming
OL,8,Fdays, bringing soaring temperatures,
OL,9,Fhumid, thundery air and some stuffy,
OL,10,Frestless nights.
OL,12,FWhere will it be hot?
OL,14,FMuch of Europe has seen temperatures
OL,15,Fin excess of 35C through the middle of
OL,16,Fthe week. Across parts of Spain,
OL,17,FPortugal and France, temperatures will
OL,18,Frocket close to 40C in the coming days
OL,19,Fwith an extensive heatwave, or 'heat
OL,20,Fdome', and heat alerts already in
OL,21,Fplace.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1781823786
OL,3,CHot with humid air: Temperatures set
OL,4,Cto reach close to 30-32C
OL,6,FParis has a chance of seeing its
OL,7,Fhottest June day on record.
OL,9,FWe will be influenced by this European
OL,10,Fheat, with temperatures set to climb
OL,11,Facross the south-east and eastern
OL,12,Fareas on Thursday and Friday.
OL,14,FTemperatures are looking to reach 27-
OL,15,F30C in many places, peaking up to 31-
OL,16,F32C (90F) on Friday, 28C on Saturday
OL,17,Fand bouncing up again to 32C on Sunday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1781823786
OL,3,CHot with humid air: Temperatures set
OL,4,Cto reach close to 30-32C
OL,6,FWith the high temperatures and strong
OL,7,Fsunshine, it'll feel increasingly
OL,8,Fmuggy, potentially making it feel
OL,9,Fhotter than conditions during the May
OL,10,Fheatwave, so expect a different feel
OL,11,Ffor many with the increasingly humid
OL,12,Fair.
OL,14,FFurther north and west, the
OL,15,Ftemperatures will stay at a more
OL,16,Fmodest level with a fresher and more
OL,17,Fcomfortable feel, together with keen,
OL,18,Fbrisk winds across Scotland and
OL,19,FNorthern Ireland.
OL,21,FWhere will it feel muggy and humid?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1781823786
OL,3,CHot with humid air: Temperatures set
OL,4,Cto reach close to 30-32C
OL,6,FThe humid air will be felt most across
OL,7,Fthe south-east and southern areas,
OL,8,Fmore so across central and inland
OL,9,Fareas, and coastal stretches will have
OL,10,Fthe chance of a freshening breeze.
OL,12,FWe had higher temperatures (35C) in
OL,13,FMay, but this humidity will add more
OL,14,Fof an uncomfortable feel - especially
OL,15,Fin urban areas - with the addition of
OL,16,Fsome warm, stuffy, restless nights.
OL,18,FOvernight temperatures on Friday night
OL,19,Fare unlikely to drop below 17/18C,
OL,20,Fhigher than some daytime temperatures
OL,21,Frecorded this month.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1781823786
OL,3,CHot with humid air: Temperatures set
OL,4,Cto reach close to 30-32C
OL,6,FNorthern and western areas will also
OL,7,Fhave some slightly muggy air by the
OL,8,Fend of the week, but it'll feel much
OL,9,Fmore manageable and comfortable in
OL,10,Fthese areas as the heat and humidity
OL,11,Fremain confined to the south-east.
OL,13,FWhy are temperatures dipping on
OL,14,FSaturday?
OL,16,FMany south-eastern areas will remain
OL,17,Fvery warm on Saturday, but not quite
OL,18,Fas hot as Friday and Sunday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1781823786
OL,3,CHot with humid air: Temperatures set
OL,4,Cto reach close to 30-32C
OL,6,FA frontal system will slip southwards
OL,7,Facross all areas, modifying the
OL,8,Fexisting hot air, together with
OL,9,Fbringing a little more cloud.
OL,11,FAs a result, temperatures will slide a
OL,12,Ffew degrees as the heat and humid air
OL,13,Ffrom Friday gives way for a time,
OL,14,Fresulting in a slightly fresher feel,
OL,15,Fbut temperatures will remain high and
OL,16,Fit will be more pleasant and
OL,17,Fmanageable conditions for many.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
