PN,31808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1781823786
OL,3,CHot with humid air: Temperatures set
OL,4,Cto reach close to 30-32C
OL,6,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,7,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,8,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,9,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,11,FBy Sunday, temperatures will be
OL,12,Fboosted once more - close to 30-32C
OL,13,Facross the south-east and this time
OL,14,Fmany south-western and central areas
OL,15,Fwill also start to feel a bit hotter
OL,16,Fas temperatures rise. Many of us will
OL,17,Fhave sunny skies with warmer
OL,18,Fconditions across the north as it
OL,19,Fheats up again further south.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1781823786
OL,3,CHot with humid air: Temperatures set
OL,4,Cto reach close to 30-32C
OL,6,FSo, finally some drier, summery
OL,7,Fweather?
OL,9,FIt's not quite the endless blue skies
OL,10,Fall day, every day of summer. UK
OL,11,Fsummers are rarely straightforward, so
OL,12,Fthere are a few obstacles to bear in
OL,13,Fmind.
OL,15,FWith the rise in humidity comes an
OL,16,Fincreased risk of thundery air.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1781823786
OL,3,CHot with humid air: Temperatures set
OL,4,Cto reach close to 30-32C
OL,6,FThunderstorms will initially develop
OL,7,Facross the continent, and there's a
OL,8,Frisk some will extend from France into
OL,9,Fsouth-eastern areas of the UK later on
OL,10,FThursday, but many areas across
OL,11,Fsouthern Britain will remain dry.
OL,13,FNorthern and western areas of the UK
OL,14,Fwill generally have a very different
OL,15,Fforecast with brisk winds, more cloud
OL,16,Fand some outbreaks of rain - mostly
OL,17,Fover parts of Scotland, Northern
OL,18,FIreland and Cumbria initially - before
OL,19,Fthe summer sunshine returns into the
OL,20,Fweekend with the best of the weather
OL,21,Fhere on Sunday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
